  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nHello! I found out that metric `validator_monitor_prev_epoch_beacon_blocks_total` always shows `0` regardless of real block produces.\r\nFor example, in ropsten validator id `101918`. We can see that it [produce last block](https://ropsten.beaconcha.in/validator/101918#blocks) at 10th August, 10:59 PM. Now, how looks `validator_monitor_prev_epoch_beacon_blocks_total` and `validator_monitor_beacon_block_total` metrics in grafana (last one works fine):\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/87700053/184248632-0c566342-eb14-4599-820f-c32322dc121a.png)\r\n\r\nSo `validator_monitor_beacon_block_total` catches a new block, but `validator_monitor_prev_epoch_beacon_blocks_total` doesn't.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ docker exec -it lighthouse_node lighthouse --version\r\nLighthouse v2.5.1-df51a73\r\nBLS library: blst-portable\r\nSHA256 hardware acceleration: false\r\nSpecs: mainnet (true), minimal (false), gnosis (true)\r\n$ docker image ls | grep light\r\nsigp/lighthouse                            v2.5.1    23b9d4a8c9d1   8 days ago     274MB\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Present Behavior\r\n\r\nMetric `validator_monitor_prev_epoch_beacon_blocks_total` always shows `0`.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThis metric should set the gauge to `1` then it saw a new block in previous epoch from monitored validator.\r\n\r\n",
